1
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:08,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I know some may feel it's too soon.</font>

2
00:00:08,470 --> 00:00:09,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However...</font>

3
00:00:09,540 --> 00:00:11,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We need even fresher concepts,</font>

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:12,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">even lighter footwork,</font>

5
00:00:12,830 --> 00:00:15,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and passion that burns even brighter!</font>

6
00:00:15,580 --> 00:00:17,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In order to meet 
our client's expectations,</font>

7
00:00:17,980 --> 00:00:23,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we've created a new team 
led by our youngest creative director.</font>

8
00:00:24,610 --> 00:00:26,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I give you Team Kamiya!</font>

9
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:30,800
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Oh, come on. This is definitely premature.</i></font>

10
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Must be nice being 
the director's favorite.</i></font>

11
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:35,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>The heck is this?</i></font>

12
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:38,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>And here I went to the trouble
 of raising a soldier...</i></font>

13
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:40,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Training him was such a waste of effort.</i></font>

14
00:00:40,730 --> 00:00:43,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Well, I bet people will have 
plenty to say about us.</i></font>

15
00:00:43,770 --> 00:00:45,770
<font size="20">PRODUCTION HQ, CREATIVE DEPT.,
1ST CREATIVE DEPT. DIVISION, TEAM KASUGA</font>

16
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:46,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}I'm glad I was able to transfer 
out of marketing, but...</i></font>

17
00:00:45,770 --> 00:00:46,860
<font size="20">COPYWRITER YURINA MITSUHASHI</font>

18
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:50,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Looks like it's gonna be rough sailing, 
don't you think, Asakura-senpai?</i></font>

19
00:00:50,490 --> 00:00:51,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Success!</font>

20
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:55,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A few words, if you would, Kamiya.</font>

21
00:00:56,670 --> 00:01:00,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm gonna tackle things head-on 
at full force to create something great.</font>

22
00:01:01,660 --> 00:01:03,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Lookin' forward to working with all of ya!</font>

23
00:02:38,550 --> 00:02:41,770
<font size="20">{\an8}EPISODE 4: WHEN YOU FIND
YOURSELF THE BEST TEAM</font>

24
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:46,150
<font size="20">KOU YATANI (24)</font>

25
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:45,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Yatani-paisen.</font>

26
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:50,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Congratulations on that job offer 
from Dai Nihon Advertisement.</font>

27
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:51,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's your starting salary?</font>

28
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:52,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hey...</font>

29
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Say, show me your job-hunting portfolio.</font>

30
00:02:55,730 --> 00:02:57,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'mma reverse engineer how you succeeded</font>

31
00:02:57,870 --> 00:03:00,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and take the shortest route 
to landing an agency gig.</font>

32
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:03,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You have a ways to go before 
you worry about job hunting.</font>

33
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">First-years should focus on coursework.</font>

34
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:08,670
<font size="20">YUSUKE KAMIYA (19)</font>

35
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:08,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Classes are so boring, though!</font>

36
00:03:08,670 --> 00:03:11,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I mean, come on, we don't do
 projects we can actually use</font>

37
00:03:11,210 --> 00:03:14,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">for job hunting until our third year? 
That's way too late.</font>

38
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:18,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did you come to art school 
purely to become a designer?</font>

39
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:20,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's a guy to do, man?</font>

40
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:23,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You gotta be an art school graduate
to get a design position at an ad agency.</font>

41
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:26,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Listen, Kamiya...</font>

42
00:03:26,390 --> 00:03:27,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's a guy named Matsuura</font>

43
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:29,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">who's looking to staff
his graduation project.</font>

44
00:03:30,350 --> 00:03:31,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why not try helping him out?</font>

45
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:32,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

46
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:38,320
<font size="20">{\an8}FILM DEPARTMENT
RECRUITING MEMBERS!</font>

47
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:35,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You've only been here half a year, huh?</font>

48
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:37,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Must be nice! You're so young.</font>

49
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:42,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Illustrator, Photoshop... 
I've mastered all the design software.</font>

50
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:42,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, wow.</font>

51
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:45,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I also have an understanding 
of video-editing software.</font>

52
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}That's exciting to hear!</font>

53
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:48,210
<font size="20">NAOKI MATSUURA (22)</font>

54
00:03:46,690 --> 00:03:48,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}In fact...</font>

55
00:03:48,210 --> 00:03:51,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I know how to do planning and PR as well,</font>

56
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">so feel free to take 
advantage of my skills.</font>

57
00:03:53,820 --> 00:03:56,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">All right, thanks. Let's make 
something really great toge—</font>

58
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:58,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's not what I meant.</font>

59
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Y'know, there're greats like Lasseter</font>

60
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:03,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">who're capable of doing 
everything by themselves.</font>

61
00:04:03,270 --> 00:04:06,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're pretty much saying you can't,
 so you need help, right?</font>

62
00:04:08,350 --> 00:04:09,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Did I piss him off?</i></font>

63
00:04:09,940 --> 00:04:11,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Oh well.</i></font>

64
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I like that!</font>

65
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:13,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

66
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:16,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The fun of working together in a group
is getting different takes on things.</font>

67
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:17,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's not—</font>

68
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:18,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, I know!</font>

69
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,160
<font size="20">{\an8}FINAL STORYBOARD, DIR. NAOKI MATSUURA
<i>A SINGLE DROP</i> MAU GRADUATION PROJECT</font>

70
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:20,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your thoughts on the presentation too?</font>

71
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:23,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yusuke, could you take a look 
at the storyboard?</font>

72
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>What the heck is up with 
this bubbly spring chicken?</i></font>

73
00:04:28,910 --> 00:04:31,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hey, where's my hair clip?</font>

74
00:04:31,550 --> 00:04:33,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh? Gotta be around there somewhere.</font>

75
00:04:34,170 --> 00:04:35,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Wait.</font>

76
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:36,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's this?</font>

77
00:04:37,770 --> 00:04:38,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">An earring, right?</font>

78
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But this is sounding 
like a trick question, so...</font>

79
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I give up!</font>

80
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:47,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You don't give a shit about me, do you?</font>

81
00:04:47,180 --> 00:04:50,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's why I told you, y'know? 
I'm not interested in dating anyone.</font>

82
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:53,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">She's not my girlfriend either.</font>

83
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:56,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But you never said anything
about there being another girl!</font>

84
00:04:56,940 --> 00:04:58,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then let's stop seeing each other.</font>

85
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:00,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Anyway, you hungry?</font>

86
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:09,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Another woman?</font>

87
00:05:09,670 --> 00:05:14,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Say, Yatani-san, why'd you tell me to help
with Matsuura-san's graduation project?</font>

88
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:17,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You know I'm better suited
to working on my own.</font>

89
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's not just you.</font>

90
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:22,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Art students in general aren't crazy 
about group projects.</font>

91
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But you know...</font>

92
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:26,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Even Lasseter who you like so much...</font>

93
00:05:26,130 --> 00:05:28,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">His truly revolutionary breakthroughs</font>

94
00:05:28,030 --> 00:05:30,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">only came when he found himself 
the best team, don't you think?</font>

95
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're too full of yourself.</font>

96
00:05:36,810 --> 00:05:38,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Learn some humility, Kamiya.</font>

97
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:43,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Screw you. It's fine.</i></font>

98
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:48,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>As long as I've got the skills, 
I'm allowed to be full of myself!</i></font>

99
00:05:54,290 --> 00:06:00,420
<font size="20">{\an8}<i>A SINGLE DROP</i> DIR. NAOKI MATSUURA
ANIMATED SHORT, MAU GRADUATION PROJECT</font>

100
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:57,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>You'd think it's a standard font,
but look closer,</i></font>

101
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>and it's been carefully manipulated 
to match the mood of the art.</i></font>

102
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>He's a first-year, yet he's capable
 of such sophisticated design.</i></font>

103
00:06:04,690 --> 00:06:08,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>He must've been studying constantly, 
even before getting into the university.</i></font>

104
00:06:10,810 --> 00:06:13,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Really impressive, Yusuke.</font>

105
00:06:13,130 --> 00:06:15,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Right? I've already made arrangements
 to submit it and—</font>

106
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:17,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But this won't do.</font>

107
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:17,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

108
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:20,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The design itself is near complete,</font>

109
00:06:20,340 --> 00:06:23,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but as it stands, it won't touch
 the audience I really want it to.</font>

110
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:25,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't follow.</font>

111
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What exactly is wrong with this poster?</font>

112
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:31,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's a bit off from 
the intended theme of the film.</font>

113
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:33,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It needs to reach my audience beyond that.</font>

114
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:34,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then <i>you</i> do it!</font>

115
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:36,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, but you can't, can ya?!</font>

116
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:37,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's why you asked me!</font>

117
00:06:37,460 --> 00:06:38,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya!</font>

118
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:40,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's right. I've asked you 
because I can't do it.</font>

119
00:06:40,910 --> 00:06:43,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But if something isn't right, 
I'm going to say so.</font>

120
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:45,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's no point 
in being a team if I don't.</font>

121
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:47,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A team?</font>

122
00:06:47,010 --> 00:06:52,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's right. As the team manager, 
I cannot approve this poster.</font>

123
00:06:57,710 --> 00:06:59,650
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yeah, yeah. Okay.</font>

124
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, and by the way...</font>

125
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:04,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm going to add your name 
to the end credits, Yusuke.</font>

126
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:07,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>He's gonna credit me in the 
special thanks with everyone else.</i></font>

127
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>How freakin' lame!</i></font>

128
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:13,410
<font size="20">{\an8}<i>A SINGLE DROP</i> DIR. NAOKI MATSUURA
ANIMATED SHORT, MAU GRADUATION PROJECT</font>

129
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:16,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This is the one! I've been curious
about it since I saw the poster.</font>

130
00:07:16,410 --> 00:07:18,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Really went all out for
a graduation project, didn't they?</font>

131
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:24,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>We will now begin the screening 
of </i>A Single Drop<i>,</i></font>

132
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:26,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>directed by Naoki Matsuura.</i></font>

133
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:56,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Yusuke, you'll shine brightly someday.</i></font>

134
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:59,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>But please don't ever forget...</i></font>

135
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:01,270
<font size="20">{\an8}PLANNING AND ORIGINAL WORK
NAOKI MATSUURA</font>

136
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:04,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Thanks to everyone involved in this,</i></font>

137
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,210
<font size="20">{\an8}SCENARIO
NAOKI MATSUURA</font>

138
00:08:02,210 --> 00:08:03,150
<font size="20">{\an8}STORYBOARD
NAOKI MATSUURA</font>

139
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,090
<font size="20">{\an8}CHARACTER DESIGN
NAOKI MATSUURA, KENSUKE SAIKATSU</font>

140
00:08:04,090 --> 00:08:05,090
<font size="20">{\an8}ORGANIZERS: DAISUKE ITOU, KANAMI UEDA,
AINE FUKUDA, YOICHIROU YAMAGUCHI</font>

141
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:07,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>and thanks to the work itself...</i></font>

142
00:08:05,090 --> 00:08:06,090
<font size="20">{\an8}CREATIVE SUPERVISOR
KOU YATANI</font>

143
00:08:06,090 --> 00:08:07,090
<font size="20">{\an8}ART DIRECTOR, DESIGNER
YUSUKE KAMIYA</font>

144
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:08,090
<font size="20">{\an8}VENUE STAFF, VOLUNTEERS FROM
THE FILM AND VIDEO DEPARTMENT</font>

145
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:11,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>We're the ones being shone upon.</i></font>

146
00:08:17,020 --> 00:08:20,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nope. Nope. Nope.</font>

147
00:08:21,090 --> 00:08:23,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Not this one either.</font>

148
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Koichi, you aren't coming up 
with enough ideas in the first place.</font>

149
00:08:26,290 --> 00:08:28,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Quit fixating on what you <i>want</i> to do.</font>

150
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:31,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also, stop giving me proposals 
that are just way over budget.</font>

151
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:32,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, sir...</font>

152
00:08:32,810 --> 00:08:34,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">As for yours, Micchan...</font>

153
00:08:34,610 --> 00:08:37,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They're all solid, but they're boring.</font>

154
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:41,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I bet you don't even have a favorite 
among them, do you?</font>

155
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:45,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You guys... Why've you both been
working independently all this time?</font>

156
00:08:46,710 --> 00:08:48,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did you say we had to do it together?</font>

157
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're a team, damn it!</font>

158
00:08:51,430 --> 00:08:53,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">S-Sorry.</font>

159
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:56,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We'll have another review tomorrow.</font>

160
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:58,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Put your heads together before then.</font>

161
00:09:02,890 --> 00:09:05,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm gonna hit the café for a bit.</font>

162
00:09:05,050 --> 00:09:06,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What? But he just told us
 to work together.</font>

163
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:11,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You've said yourself that you focus
 better alone, right, Asakura-san?</font>

164
00:09:11,330 --> 00:09:14,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You think everything 
Kamiya-san says is right?</font>

165
00:09:14,070 --> 00:09:16,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I-I don't, but...</font>

166
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:19,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We've gotta try everything we can—</font>

167
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

168
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:30,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're spouting some real naïve baloney, 
aren't you?</font>

169
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:33,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You think you run a team?</font>

170
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:35,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What you need are soldiers.</font>

171
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:37,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You learned that under me, didn't you?</font>

172
00:09:37,470 --> 00:09:40,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yeah, I know that's
 your style, Yanagi-san.</font>

173
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But the way I do things—</font>

174
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:44,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You already know, don't you?</font>

175
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:47,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You and I are alike.</font>

176
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:50,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You couldn't possibly understand
those who can't hack it.</font>

177
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Stuff it.</font>

178
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, there you are!</font>

179
00:09:55,540 --> 00:09:56,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya-san!</font>

180
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:58,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Director Furuya's looking for you.</font>

181
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:00,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He says to wear a jacket.</font>

182
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:09,630
<font size="20">PRODUCTION HQ, SALES PROMOTION DEPT.
DIRECTOR YUJIRO SHIRAI</font>

183
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:08,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Kamiya, you really saved me the other day.</font>

184
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:09,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Likewise, sir.</font>

185
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:13,010
<font size="20">MEDIA HQ, MEDIA DEPT.
DIRECTOR TAKUYA MIYOSHI</font>

186
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:13,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}So <i>you're</i> Kamiya-kun, eh?
A real handsome fella.</font>

187
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:18,010
<font size="20">PRODUCTION HQ, MARKETING DEPT.
DIRECTOR REN KUSUNOSE</font>

188
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:15,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}I hear you've been taking good care 
of Micchan over there.</font>

189
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:18,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Tell her she can come back anytime.</font>

190
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:21,770
<font size="20">SALES HQ, 1ST SALES DEPT.
DIRECTOR KAORU GOURIKI</font>

191
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:20,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Hey, Kamiya, how old are ya?</font>

192
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:21,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}I'm 33.</font>

193
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:25,150
<font size="20">SALES HQ, SALES PROMOTION DEPT.
DIRECTOR SEIJI IORI</font>

194
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:24,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}That's nice. A young man indeed.</font>

195
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:28,520
<font size="20">PRODUCTION HQ, CREATIVE DEPT.
DIRECTOR SHO FURUYA</font>

196
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:28,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Sorry to pull you aside
when you're busy, Kamiya.</font>

197
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:34,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Six directors in one room means...</i></font>

198
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:38,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's no point in wasting precious time.</font>

199
00:10:38,230 --> 00:10:41,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'll get straight to the point
and start with the conclusion.</font>

200
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:46,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm temporarily disbanding Team Kamiya.</font>

201
00:10:50,170 --> 00:10:54,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm temporarily disbanding Team Kamiya.</font>

202
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:56,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why?!</font>

203
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ya listen here!</font>

204
00:10:57,740 --> 00:11:01,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The beverage giant, Sunny Try, has asked us
to participate in a competition.</font>

205
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:02,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They're offering 300 million!</font>

206
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They specifically requested the winner</font>

207
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:06,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">of the JAGDA Newcomer Award, 
Yusuke Kamiya!</font>

208
00:11:06,410 --> 00:11:10,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But isn't Dai-Nihon Advertisement 
their exclusive agency?</font>

209
00:11:10,090 --> 00:11:14,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Apparently, the president of Sunny Try 
is stepping down in the next few years.</font>

210
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:18,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The next president won't be his son,
but their current general manager.</font>

211
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:20,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And that's who authorized this.</font>

212
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:25,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's common for a company 
to shake up business partners</font>

213
00:11:25,030 --> 00:11:26,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">with a leadership change.</font>

214
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:28,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In other words,
this 300-million-yen competition</font>

215
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:30,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">is a showcase for the incoming president.</font>

216
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:35,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We speculate that they're in search
 of their next exclusive partner.</font>

217
00:11:35,130 --> 00:11:40,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And Sunny Try's annual advertising
 and promotional budget is 23 billion yen.</font>

218
00:11:40,890 --> 00:11:44,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya... You understand
 the gravity of that figure, don't you?</font>

219
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:48,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It will shift the power balance 
in the advertisement industry.</font>

220
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:51,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I understand. However—</font>

221
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Who asked for yer damn opinion, Kamiya?!</font>

222
00:11:53,530 --> 00:11:55,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If we win this, we storm the industry!</font>

223
00:11:55,530 --> 00:11:57,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If we lose, then we fall!</font>

224
00:11:57,150 --> 00:12:00,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Meaning this is war, damn it!</font>

225
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:02,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Now, now, Director Gouriki.</font>

226
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:05,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We only have this opportunity
thanks to Kamiya here, after all.</font>

227
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:11,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We'll assemble top talent from 
every section and create a task force.</font>

228
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:15,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya, you'll focus your efforts there.</font>

229
00:12:16,580 --> 00:12:19,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>The second we get a huge project, 
</i>this<i> happens?</i></font>

230
00:12:19,690 --> 00:12:21,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I mean, yeah...</i></font>

231
00:12:21,330 --> 00:12:23,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Those guys are still nowhere near ready.</i></font>

232
00:12:23,730 --> 00:12:27,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>You couldn't possibly understand
those who can't hack it.</i></font>

233
00:12:28,810 --> 00:12:32,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Indeed, I suppose this competition 
would be too much for such a young team.</font>

234
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:36,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">After all, there's
 23 billion yen at stake.</font>

235
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I understand how you must feel.</font>

236
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:42,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But let's be adults here, Yusuke.</font>

237
00:12:42,950 --> 00:12:47,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Asakura and Mitsuhashi will move
to Terada's team for the time being.</font>

238
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:49,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You will lead the task force, and—</font>

239
00:12:49,910 --> 00:12:51,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Please give me five minutes!</font>

240
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:56,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'll explain why we should be 
doing this with my current team!</font>

241
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:00,590
<font size="20">{\an8}POSSIBILITY</font>

242
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:02,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">According to your speculation,</font>

243
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:08,350
<font size="20">{\an8}"COMPETITION TO FIND EXCLUSIVE PARTNER"
NEW PRESIDENT, 23 BILLION ON THE TABLE</font>

244
00:13:02,130 --> 00:13:06,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the incoming president is doing this
to find a new exclusive agency.</font>

245
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:08,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Were there any project specs?</font>

246
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:10,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We've yet to find that out.</font>

247
00:13:10,810 --> 00:13:13,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But you surely have a rough idea, no?</font>

248
00:13:13,050 --> 00:13:15,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A TV commercial or poster. 
Perhaps an in-store POP display.</font>

249
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:18,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nine times out of ten, it's a poster.</font>

250
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:19,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">How are you so certain?</font>

251
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:21,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You aren't just spitting BS, are ya?!</font>

252
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:25,370
<font size="20">{\an8}JAGDA NEWCOMER AWARD</font>

253
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:25,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They reached out to us after seeing 
the JAGDA Newcomer Awards, right?</font>

254
00:13:25,830 --> 00:13:29,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Which means this project will be close
 to what I submitted for the award.</font>

255
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, I suppose so.</font>

256
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:34,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But in that case, 
don't you find it strange?</font>

257
00:13:34,130 --> 00:13:36,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">300 mil for a poster is
way too much.</font>

258
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:39,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Sunny Try has 23 billion yen
 to spend, you know?</font>

259
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:42,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Whether it's 30 million or 300 million,
it makes little difference to them.</font>

260
00:13:42,380 --> 00:13:46,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Director Iori, you've been in charge 
of Sunny Try before, haven't you?</font>

261
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:48,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Are they so fast and loose with money?</font>

262
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:51,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No, Sunny Try is very strict 
when it comes to money.</font>

263
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:53,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In fact, they're so versed with ads,</font>

264
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:55,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">they know exactly 
what a fair price is.</font>

265
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:57,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then why set it at 300 million?</font>

266
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:59,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You'd better be getting at something here!</font>

267
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:02,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's an experiment.</font>

268
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:06,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The incoming president of Sunny Try, 
a peer in the same industry,</font>

269
00:14:06,810 --> 00:14:09,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">couldn't possibly be unaware 
of a certain experiment conducted</font>

270
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:12,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">by a major overseas competitor
since January, right?</font>

271
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:15,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A super-scale marketing 
demonstration experiment...</font>

272
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:17,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The heck is that?</font>

273
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:20,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">For many years, said company has invested</font>

274
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">over 70 percent of its advertising budget 
into commercials alone.</font>

275
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:25,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However, they formulated a hypothesis</font>

276
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:28,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">that outdoor ads throughout the city
would be more effective</font>

277
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:31,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">than TV ads, since they're 
so close to the point of sale.</font>

278
00:14:31,930 --> 00:14:34,310
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And so they proceeded to experiment.</font>

279
00:14:34,310 --> 00:14:46,570
<font size="20">{\an8}OTHER, OUTDOOR ADS, TV COMMERCIALS</font>

280
00:14:34,310 --> 00:14:36,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">For half of the experimental period,</font>

281
00:14:36,130 --> 00:14:38,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">commercials were kept 
to 40 percent or less of the budget,</font>

282
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">with the rest going
to outdoor ads and such.</font>

283
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:44,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">For the other half, they did their usual
and spent 70 percent on TV commercials.</font>

284
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:46,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">With the insights they gained from this,</font>

285
00:14:46,570 --> 00:14:50,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">they revised their marketing strategy, 
and the result was...</font>

286
00:14:51,980 --> 00:14:54,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">their highest profits in 30 years!</font>

287
00:14:57,210 --> 00:14:59,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're saying Sunny Try's 
300-million-yen competition</font>

288
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:03,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">is an in-house experiment of its own 
following this approach?</font>

289
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:06,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That would require a ridiculous amount 
of time and resources.</font>

290
00:15:06,450 --> 00:15:08,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's far beyond a mere showcase!</font>

291
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:09,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's right!</font>

292
00:15:09,330 --> 00:15:13,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The incoming president isn't just looking 
for someone to do business with.</font>

293
00:15:13,820 --> 00:15:18,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He's looking for a new partner
who'll fight alongside him!</font>

294
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:19,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Which is precisely why—</font>

295
00:15:20,430 --> 00:15:22,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Impressive insight. 
Taking this into account,</font>

296
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I absolutely want you on the task force.</font>

297
00:15:25,190 --> 00:15:29,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You think even the current Team Kamiya 
can handle it if it's a poster?</font>

298
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Indeed, perhaps they can.</font>

299
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:33,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However, that alone isn't going to cut it.</font>

300
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let us exhaust all of our options!</font>

301
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:38,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Come up with wild schemes! 
Secret plans! Brilliant plots!</font>

302
00:15:38,090 --> 00:15:41,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Think of every possible plan 
we can implement!</font>

303
00:15:42,310 --> 00:15:44,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And what is that going to get you?</font>

304
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:48,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A whole bunch of massive meetings, 
stacks of thick documents,</font>

305
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:50,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and ass-kissing for ulterior motives.</font>

306
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:54,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Director Furuya, this conference room
is a microrepresentation</font>

307
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:56,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">of your traditional 
ad agency organization!</font>

308
00:15:58,450 --> 00:16:01,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's right. 
And you're a part of that too.</font>

309
00:16:01,910 --> 00:16:04,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You'd try to deny that now?</font>

310
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm not gonna completely deny it.</font>

311
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:10,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But that's not what Sunny Try 
is looking for right now!</font>

312
00:16:11,490 --> 00:16:13,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then what are they looking for?</font>

313
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:16,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">An even fresher concept!</font>

314
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:17,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Even lighter footwork!</font>

315
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:19,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And passion that burns even brighter!</font>

316
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:24,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's how you described my team 
the day we formed.</font>

317
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:28,800
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We're a small, elite group 
in a boutique agency!</font>

318
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:33,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Even if it was just lip service, 
you said it yourself, didn't ya?!</font>

319
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:43,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The official assignment
 is still a little ways off,</font>

320
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:45,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but I'll block off time 
for an orientation, okay?</font>

321
00:16:45,570 --> 00:16:46,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">All right.</font>

322
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:47,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hey, Kamiya.</font>

323
00:16:47,620 --> 00:16:48,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's up?</font>

324
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:52,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You got pretty fresh
with Furuya-san in there, didn't ya?</font>

325
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:52,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh...</font>

326
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:55,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well, butting heads isn't all that bad.</font>

327
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:58,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The ground hardens 
after the rain, as they say.</font>

328
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:07,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're not capitalizing 
on each other's strengths at all.</font>

329
00:17:08,270 --> 00:17:10,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You need to voice your opinions more.</font>

330
00:17:10,470 --> 00:17:13,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You really think we're gonna win 
the Sunny Try competition with this?</font>

331
00:17:14,690 --> 00:17:16,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You wanna just go back to marketing?</font>

332
00:17:17,350 --> 00:17:20,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Director Kusunose said 
you'd be welcome anytime.</font>

333
00:17:20,670 --> 00:17:23,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Are ya even motivated enough 
to do creative work?</font>

334
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:26,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I am. Plus, I'm learning different things!</font>

335
00:17:26,050 --> 00:17:27,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't learn on the job!</font>

336
00:17:28,610 --> 00:17:31,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your job is to generate 
good ideas with confidence.</font>

337
00:17:31,630 --> 00:17:34,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I bet you don't even like your own ideas.</font>

338
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Who cares whether I like them or not?</font>

339
00:17:36,970 --> 00:17:39,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What matters is whether the client does.</font>

340
00:17:39,020 --> 00:17:40,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">M-Micchan...</font>

341
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:45,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then which one do you think 
the client would like most?</font>

342
00:17:46,620 --> 00:17:50,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That would be... the third one, I guess.</font>

343
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:54,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Not bad, but it'll get buried 
among all the other ads.</font>

344
00:17:54,010 --> 00:17:55,510
<font size="20">{\an8}THE BODY, ENERGIZED.</font>

345
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:55,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What do you think, Koichi?</font>

346
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:58,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Um, well, let's see...</font>

347
00:17:58,230 --> 00:18:01,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This looks like it would need
a restrained logo design.</font>

348
00:18:01,210 --> 00:18:03,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'd want a crazier idea!</font>

349
00:18:03,390 --> 00:18:05,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What do you mean by "crazier"?</font>

350
00:18:05,740 --> 00:18:09,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You know. Like, an idea that
 breaks the mold.</font>

351
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You mean like thinking outside the box?</font>

352
00:18:11,940 --> 00:18:13,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yeah, exactly.</font>

353
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:18,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then we need to define our box
before I can figure out what's outside it.</font>

354
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:21,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Don't give me that "you're right!" look.</i></font>

355
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:25,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Micchan, could you teach me 
how to define the box?</font>

356
00:18:25,140 --> 00:18:27,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Excuse me? I'm the junior here, y'know.</font>

357
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:31,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yeah, but lately, I've been thinking 
none of that matters.</font>

358
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then treat me to something, okay?</font>

359
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:37,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Aw, come on. Lunch at the minimum!</font>

360
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:42,180
<font size="20">{\an8}GENERATE FREE & FLEXIBLE IDEAS,
UNCONSTRAINED BY EXISTING CONVENTION</font>

361
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ya ready? Listen up.</font>

362
00:18:39,010 --> 00:18:43,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">To begin with, your framework
is a key point to consider.</font>

363
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:44,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And you can map this all out...</font>

364
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:46,310
<font size="20">{\an8}GOOD MIXER, POST-WORKOUT,
EASY TO DRINK WITH MEALS</font>

365
00:18:46,310 --> 00:18:48,060
<font size="20">{\an8}FEATURES, USABLE SCENES,
EMOTIONAL IMAGE, CONSUMER OPINION</font>

366
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:52,740
<font size="20">{\an8}NEEDS MORE THRILL. A RUSH.
ANY OTHER TAKES? TOO CONVENTIONAL</font>

367
00:18:59,830 --> 00:19:00,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We won.</font>

368
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:05,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That 300-million Sunny Try presentation?</font>

369
00:19:05,790 --> 00:19:06,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They said we got the job.</font>

370
00:19:10,990 --> 00:19:12,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">See, you got this.</font>

371
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You've got the guts, after all.</font>

372
00:19:14,730 --> 00:19:16,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Th-Thank you very much!</font>

373
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:23,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya-san, Director Furuya is—</font>

374
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:26,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yeah, yeah, I figured you'd show up.</font>

375
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:28,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You seem like you're 
in a good mood today.</font>

376
00:19:28,530 --> 00:19:30,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No jacket required.</font>

377
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I know.</font>

378
00:19:34,650 --> 00:19:37,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I thought you were on board with us.</font>

379
00:19:40,030 --> 00:19:44,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Changing the team could potentially leave 
a bad impression on the client, you know?</font>

380
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:47,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The company understands that.</font>

381
00:19:47,570 --> 00:19:51,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Which is why I want you to be the 
creative director of the task force.</font>

382
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:54,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I want to do this with my current team.</font>

383
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:57,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Those guys have grown.</font>

384
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:58,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">More than the competition, we'll—</font>

385
00:19:58,640 --> 00:19:59,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya!</font>

386
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:03,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">"The Sunny Try project will be 
handled by a specialized team,</font>

387
00:20:03,390 --> 00:20:05,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">with the entire company 
ready to back them up."</font>

388
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:09,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It wasn't my decision. It came from above.</font>

389
00:20:09,270 --> 00:20:11,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">From above you, Director?</font>

390
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:12,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did the executive in charge...</font>

391
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:15,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It was the president's order.</font>

392
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:17,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No one can defy that.</font>

393
00:20:20,890 --> 00:20:22,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's the nature of the organization.</font>

394
00:20:22,970 --> 00:20:27,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ad agencies don't change so easily.</font>

395
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:32,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya, you'll stay here 
and fight alongside me, won't you?</font>

396
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:38,050
<font size="20">{\an8}THE BODY, ENERGIZED.</font>

397
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Man, that's bold.</font>

398
00:20:37,770 --> 00:20:39,800
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's definitely different.</font>

399
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:42,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It feels like it could use 
some more refining...</font>

400
00:20:42,690 --> 00:20:43,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">More than this?</font>

401
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:46,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No, no, it looks perfect.</font>

402
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:49,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">His truly revolutionary breakthroughs</font>

403
00:20:49,130 --> 00:20:51,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">only came when he found himself 
the best team, don't you think?</font>

404
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:56,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Excuse me for a bit.</font>

405
00:20:57,530 --> 00:20:59,570
<font size="20">{\an8}KOU YATANI</font>

406
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:02,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yo, Koichi.</font>

407
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:04,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Kamiya-san.</font>

408
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:05,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're still working at this hour?</font>

409
00:21:05,810 --> 00:21:06,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Something like that.</font>

410
00:21:07,580 --> 00:21:09,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, yeah, about that Sunny Try project...</font>

411
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:14,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We decided to use your logo as-is.</font>

412
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:18,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm sure you don't know what to say
given you're off the project.</font>

413
00:21:18,350 --> 00:21:19,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm so glad...</font>

414
00:21:20,940 --> 00:21:23,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I was able to help 
in some way after all, huh?</font>

415
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:25,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Koichi...</font>

416
00:21:25,140 --> 00:21:28,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm so glad I was able
 to work with our team!</font>

417
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:32,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>We're the people behind the scenes.</i></font>

418
00:21:33,780 --> 00:21:39,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Most creative works in the world 
don't get attributed to anyone specific.</i></font>

419
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:42,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That's especially true for advertising.</i></font>

420
00:21:43,180 --> 00:21:45,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>As long as it gets out there,
 that's enough.</i></font>

421
00:21:50,450 --> 00:21:52,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Even if no one knows...</i></font>

422
00:21:53,150 --> 00:21:54,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>who created it.</i></font>

423
00:21:58,300 --> 00:22:00,800
<font size="20">{\an8}THE BODY, ENERGIZED.</font>

424
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You suck.</font>

425
00:22:09,460 --> 00:22:11,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A man's path blurred by tears...</font>

426
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:19,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>A man's path blurred by tears...</i></font>

427
00:22:24,530 --> 00:22:28,240
<font size="20">{\an8}TRANSLATION: YUKARI MURASE-LOUDEN</font>

